{
  "texts": [
    "LLMs can be trained on a variety of datasets, extending beyond web-scraped data to include proprietary datasets such as medical records, as demonstrated by models like GatorTron and ClinicalT5 22.",
    "Additionally, LLMs are just one type of generative AI; other models, such as vision-language models (VLMs) and generative adversarial networks (GANs), can also be trained on diverse multi-modal datasets 22, 23.",
    "However, there is often a lack of adequate transparency regarding the architecture, training methods, and datasets used to train many of the most popular commercial LLMs.",
    "This makes it more difficult to understand and anticipate risks compared to open-source models that provide more information about their model weights, training data, and methodologies, which may enable better understanding and verification of their capabilities and limitations [24] [25] [26].",
    "While developers have provided high-level information about structure and functionality, critical elements such as data cards, model cards, and bias cards-proposed by AI researchers-are not always shared alongside a model."
  ]
}